trans-unit.source: Represents a media type with an additional quality factor used in a Content-Type header.

The <xref:System.Net.Http.Headers.MediaTypeWithQualityHeaderValue> class provides support for the media type and quality in a Content-Type header as defined in [RFC 2616](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=241642) by the IETF.
Quality factors allow the user agent to indicate the relative degree of preference for the media type in a Content-Type header.
Quality uses a scale from 0 to 1.
The default value is q=1.
This type derives from <xref:System.Net.Http.Headers.MediaTypeHeaderValue>.
